3) CLI and Runtime Behavior (exact observed behavior from src/lib/main.js)
- Exports: named exports fizzBuzz and fizzBuzzSingle are re-exported from src/lib/main.js.
- CLI entry: when executed as a script (node src/lib/main.js) the module runs cli(process.argv.slice(2)).
- Supported CLI usages (matching usage() output):
  node src/lib/main.js --single N
  node src/lib/main.js --range N
  node src/lib/main.js N
  node src/lib/main.js start end
- Flag semantics:
  --single N or --single=N : prints the single fizzBuzzSingle(N) value then exits. If N === 0, prints nothing and exits 0.
  --range N or --range=N  : prints fizzBuzz(N) lines (1..N). If N === 0, prints nothing and exits 0.
- Positional semantics:
  Single positional N prints fizzBuzz(N) (one-per-line) except N === 0 prints nothing.
  Two positionals start end: validates start >= 1 and end >= start, prints lines for inclusive range start..end using fizzBuzzSingle(i).
- Input validation/errors:
  Missing required numeric tokens or non-integer tokens throw TypeError with messages: "n is required" or "n must be an integer".
  Negative or out-of-range numeric inputs produce RangeError (per MISSION tests).
  Any thrown error prints concise err.message to stderr and sets process.exitCode = 1.

