9) Reference Details (API signatures, CLI flags, config keys, exact return types)
- Library API (exact signatures and behaviors):
  fizzBuzz(n)
    Parameters: n (integer)
    Returns: Array of strings of length n (if n >= 1), each element is either the decimal string of the integer or "Fizz"/"Buzz"/"FizzBuzz" per divisibility rules.
    Edge cases: n === 0 -> returns [] ; n < 0 -> throw RangeError ; non-integer -> throw TypeError

  fizzBuzzSingle(n)
    Parameters: n (integer)
    Returns: string representing single-value substitutions: "Fizz" if divisible by 3, "Buzz" if divisible by 5, "FizzBuzz" if divisible by both, otherwise decimal string of n.
    Edge cases: negative input -> RangeError ; non-integer -> TypeError

- CLI flags and semantics (exact forms accepted):
  --single=N or --single N  -> prints fizzBuzzSingle(N) then exits. N===0 -> prints nothing.
  --range=N or --range N    -> prints fizzBuzz(N) lines in order 1..N. N===0 -> prints nothing.
  Positional single N       -> prints fizzBuzz(N) (one-per-line)
  Positional start end      -> prints fizzBuzzSingle(i) for each i in inclusive range start..end after validation start>=1 and end>=start

- Error messages (exact strings produced by parseIntegerToken and usage):
  When token missing: "n is required"
  When token not integer: "n must be an integer"
  When start < 1: "start must be >= 1"
  When end < start: "end must be >= start"

